 Spokesperson for the Department of Safety, Security and Liaison, Mr Moeti Mmusi, said that an investigation is underway but it’s alleged that a taxi tried to overtake a truck. The driver saw an oncoming car and tried to revert back into the lane and then collided with the side of the truck.  The taxi was occupied by three people, one passenger died in the accident but no other injuries have been reported. The accident caused a delay in traffic on the Loskop road but is now open for use.   Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za